<subSubSection id="11B0062888293DC05079AD1925D673DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" type="notes">
<paragraph id="658D28B197EFA0EE29C29181C8792445" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18F948A7E45970BF137C1FC0AC548C4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="FFF4AF5B989F8C1B4E134D1F95D91465" authorityName="Nobis &amp; Krzempek &amp; Nowak &amp; Gudkova &amp; Klichowska" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="M. Nobis, P. D. Gudkova, Krzempek &amp; Klichowska, comb. and" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stipa purpurea subsp. var. var. arenosa" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="purpurea" subSpecies="var." variety="arenosa">Stipa purpurea var. arenosa</taxonomicName>
was described, based on two collections of W.J. Roborowski from Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="951C8765E6821278E2C9775FFBD18964" author="Tzvelev, NN" editor="Grubov, VI" journalOrPublisher="Po materialam Botanicheskogo Instituta im. Komarova VL (Plantae Asiae Centralis, secus materies Instituti botanici nomine Komarovii VL), 4. Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 243" refId="B61" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1968. Zlaki (Gramineae). In: Grubov, VI, Ed., Rastieniya Centralnoi Azii. Po materialam Botanicheskogo Instituta im. Komarova VL (Plantae Asiae Centralis, secus materies Instituti botanici nomine Komarovii VL), 4. Nauka, Leningrad: 1 - 243" title="Zlaki (Gramineae)." volumeTitle="Rastieniya Centralnoi Azii." year="1968">Tzvelev 1968</bibRefCitation>
). During our research in 2009-2021, in addition to the holotype, we found four sheets (paratypes) with specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="D1D102D019F068421E25D8D2CA3B2923" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stipa" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B99D4617C90E54F396DCC8561B302FDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Stipa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by Roborowski in 1894. The two of the paratypes preserved in LE, were labeled as the type and isotype of 
<taxonomicName id="478D21093CAE3ED847BF76CB0B82729A" authorityName="Nobis &amp; Krzempek &amp; Nowak &amp; Gudkova &amp; Klichowska" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="M. Nobis, P. D. Gudkova, Krzempek &amp; Klichowska, comb. and" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stipa purpurea subsp. var. var. arenosa" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="purpurea" subSpecies="var." variety="arenosa">Stipa purpurea var. arenosa</taxonomicName>
by N. Tzvelev in 1966.
</paragraph>
